  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "sC+uu0wINikfojTvfbXv0/D4MS0=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Explicit non-goals\n\nThe design lists what live collaboration will *not* include, to prevent scope creep and clarify the minimum viable loop:\n\n- **No cursor tracking, caret overlays, or per-editor presence.** Custom editors (canvases, tables, button grids) make a generic cursor notion meaningless. It would need per-editor implementation and was a misread of the user's actual goal.\n- **No typing indicators.** Already scratched at the chat level for the same reason \u2014 latency beats the signal, so the indicator is wrong more often than it's right.\n- **No custom CRDTs or merge logic.** The reactor's operation model is the conflict resolver. Adding a CRDT layer on top would duplicate responsibility.\n- **No server-side relay.** Fully peer-to-peer via Bee nodes. No central aggregator, no sync service.\n- **No chat-level presence dots.**\n- **No \"save point\" or \"version\" layer beyond the existing keyframe/operation model.**\n\nNon-goals restated at the end of the doc as a guardrail. The single live surface is the toolbar History view, which updates with each peer's ops attributed by signer address.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
    }
  },
